Content: Bathymetry compilation for Arthur Harbor near Palmer Station, Antarctica

This data set was acquired with a Furuno FL6600 Echosounder Sonar, Furuno FCV582L Echosounder Sonar, Garmin 12 Navigation system, and Marine Sonic Technology, Ltd. Sidescan Sonar assembled as part of the 2005 Palmer_Gallager data compilation (Chief Scientist: Dr. Scott Gallagher; Investigator(s): Dr. Scott Gallagher and Dr. Vernon Asper). These data files are of Text File (ASCII) format and include gridded Bathymetry data and were processed after data collection. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): PRIMO.

Processed submersible Multibeam Sonar Data from the Lau Back-arc Basin acquired during the Melville expedition TUIM05MV (2005)

This data set was acquired with a Simrad SM2000 Multibeam Sonar system on the ROV Jason II during Melville expedition TUIM05MV conducted in 2005 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Margaret Tivey; Investigator(s): Dr. Vicki Ferrini and Dr. Margaret Tivey). These data files are of Text File (ASCII) format and include Swath Bathymetry data and were processed after data collection. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): Sampling and Initial Characterization of Hydrothermal Fluids, Deposits, Microfauna and Megafauna at Vent Fields along the Eastern Lau Spreading Center and Venture Deep Ocean, Lau Basin Expedition 3 of 5, and funding was provided by NSF grant(s): OCE02-41250, OCE02-41796, OCE02-41826, OCE02-42038, OCE02-42088, and OCE03-28117. This data was cited by Ferrini et al., 2008.

Ship-based Subbottom Seismic Shot Data acquired during the Nathaniel B. Palmer expedition NBP0507 (2005)

This data set was acquired with a ship-based ODEC Bathy2000 Subbottom Seismic system during Nathaniel B. Palmer expedition NBP0507 conducted in 2005 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Marcel Croon; Investigator(s): Dr. Steve Cande and Dr. Joann Stock). These data files are of SEGY format and include Active Subbottom Seismic shot data that have not been processed. Funding was provided by NSF grant(s): ANT03-38317 and OPP03-38346.

Processed Gridded ship-based Bathymetric Sonar Data (EM302 and EM710) from the Perth Canyon acquired during the Falkor expedition FK150301 (2015)

This data set was acquired with a ship-based Kongsberg EM302 Multibeam Sonar system and Kongsberg EM710 Multibeam Sonar system during Falkor expedition FK150301 conducted in 2015 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Malcolm McCulloch). These data files are of GeoTIFF (Raster) format and include gridded Bathymetry data and were processed after data collection. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): Perth Canyon: First Deep Exploration.

Underway Hydrographic, Weather and Ship-state Data (JGOFS) from the Argentine Basin acquired during the Nathaniel B. Palmer expedition NBP1510 (2015)

This data set was acquired with a ship-based Meteorological Sensor, Echosounder Sonar, Fluorometer, Thermosalinograph, and Navigation system during Nathaniel B. Palmer expedition NBP1510 conducted in 2015 (Chief Scientist: Dr. MIchael Kelly). These data files are of JGOFS (ASCII) format and include Fluorescence, Meteorological, Conductivity, Salinity, Bathymetry, Temperature, Visible Radiation, Infrared Radiation, and Navigation data and were processed after data collection. This data set was created from calibrated data decimated at 1-minute intervals. Several fields are derived measurements from more than a single raw input.

Raw Multi-Channel Seismic Shot Data from the Newport Inglewood/Rose Canyon and Oceanside Blind Thrust fault systems, offshore California, acquired during the R/V Melville expedition MV1316 (2013)

This data set was acquired with the Scripps Portable Multi-Channel Seismic system during R/V Melville expedition MV1316 conducted in 2013 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Neal Driscoll; Investigators: Dr. Graham Kent, Dr. Neal Driscoll). These data files are of SEGY format and include Multi-Channel Reflection Seismic shot data that have not been processed. Data were acquired as part of the project: a 2D shallow seismic survey of the Newport Inglewood/Rose Canyon and Oceanside Blind Thrust fault systems in the vicinity of the San Onofre Nuclear Generating Station (SONGS), and funding was from Southern California Edison.

Seismic Shot Point Navigation Data from offshore California acquired during R/V Melville expedition MV1316 (2013)

This data set was acquired with the Scripps Portable Multi-Channel Seismic system during R/V Melville expedition MV1316 conducted in 2013 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Neal Driscoll; Investigators: Dr. Graham Kent, Dr. Neal Driscoll). These data files are of Text (ASCII) format and include Seismic Shot Time Navigation data that were processed after data collection. These data files provide the primary seismic navigation source for this cruise. Data were acquired as part of the project: a 2D shallow seismic survey of the Newport Inglewood/Rose Canyon and Oceanside Blind Thrust fault systems in the vicinity of the San Onofre Nuclear Generating Station (SONGS), and funding was from Southern California Edison.

Processed ship-based Swath Bathymetry and Acoustic Backscatter (GSF Format) Data (EM302) from the Timor Sea acquired during the Falkor expedition FK150410 (2015)

This data set was acquired with a ship-based Kongsberg EM302 Multibeam Sonar system during Falkor expedition FK150410 conducted in 2015 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Gregory Ivey). These data files are of MBSystem Compatible format and include Swath Bathymetry and Acoustic Backscatter data and were processed at sea using the open source MB-System multibeam sonar processing software. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): Timor Sea Reef Connections.

Processed Gridded towed Sidescan Sonar Data from the Izu-Bonin-Mariana Arc: Mariana Volcanic Arc acquired during the Thomas G. Thompson expedition TN273 (2011)

This data set was acquired with a towed UH:HMRG IMI30 Sidescan Sonar on IMI30 during Thomas G. Thompson expedition TN273 conducted in 2011 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Fernando Martinez; Investigator(s): Dr. Fernando Martinez, Dr. Robert Stern, and Dr. Katherine Kelley). These data files are of NetCDF Grid format and include gridded Phase Bathymetry data and were processed after data collection. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): Collaborative Research: The Southeast Mariana Forearc Rifts and the Southernmost Mariana Trough Spreading Center: New Insights into the Tectonics and Magmatism of Intraoceanic Arcs, and funding was provided by NSF grant(s): OCE09-61352, OCE09-61559, and OCE09-61811.

HMRG Charts (PDF Format) corresponding to processed towed Sidescan Sonar Grids collected using IMI30 (Sled) from the Izu-Bonin-Mariana Arc: Mariana Volcanic Arc acquired during the Thomas G. Thompson expedition TN273 (2011)

This data set contains HMRG charts that correspond with gridded content acquired with towed UH:HMRG IMI30 Sidescan Sonar (Sled) during Thomas G. Thompson expedition TN273 conducted in 2011 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Fernando Martinez; Investigator(s): Dr. Fernando Martinez, Dr. Robert Stern, and Dr. Katherine Kelley). These data files are of PDF format and include Sidescan images and were processed after data collection. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): Collaborative Research: The Southeast Mariana Forearc Rifts and the Southernmost Mariana Trough Spreading Center: New Insights into the Tectonics and Magmatism of Intraoceanic Arcs, and funding was provided by NSF grant(s): OCE09-61352, OCE09-61559, and OCE09-61811.

Processed Bottom Pressure Recorder (BPR) data from uncabled instruments deployed at Axial Seamount on the Juan de Fuca Ridge (investigator Chris Fox)

Bottom Pressure Recorder (BPR) data from autonomous, moored, uncabled instruments deployed at Axial Seamount on the Juan de Fuca Ridge between 1997-1998. The raw pressure data recorded in psi have been converted to depth in meters by multiplying psi values by 0.67. Each ASCII file is the data from one BPR deployment, recorded every 15 seconds, with LPF depths recorded each hour on the hour. Files include: date/time, raw-depth, temperature, Spotl-detided-depth, Low-pass-filter-detided-depth. See associated documentation for deployment locations and other metadata. The BPR instruments were built by NOAA/PMEL. Funding provided by NOAA/PMEL (investigator Chris Fox). Earlier BPR data from Axial Seamount are also available at the NOAA National Centers for Environmental Information (http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/nndc/struts/results?&t=102597&s=1&d=1).

Underway Hydrographic, Weather and Ship-state Data (JGOFS) from the Antarctic Peninsula acquired during the Laurence M. Gould expedition LMG1505B (2015)

This data set was acquired with a ship-based Thermosalinograph, Fluorometer, Echosounder Sonar, MeteorologicalSensor, and Navigation system during Laurence M. Gould expedition LMG1505B conducted in 2015. These data files are of JGOFS (ASCII) format and include Navigation, Bathymetry, Visible Radiation, Salinity, Meteorological, Temperature, Infrared Radiation, Conductivity, and Fluorescence data and were processed after data collection. This data set was created from calibrated data decimated at 1-minute intervals. Several fields are derived measurements from more than a single raw input.

Processed ship-based GSF-Format Bathymetric Sonar Data (EM302) from the Sumatra-Andaman Subduction Zone acquired during Falkor expedition FK150523 (2015)

This data set was acquired with a ship-based Kongsberg EM302 Multibeam Sonar system during Falkor expedition FK150523 conducted in 2015 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Kerry Sieh). These processed swath data files are of MBSystem Compatible format and include Swath Bathymetry data. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): Mentawai Gap-Tsunami Earthquake Risk Assessment (MEGA-TERA).

Raw Multi-Channel Seismic Shot Data from the Mediterranean Sea acquired during the R/V Marcus G. Langseth expedition MGL1521 (2015)

This data set was acquired with the Lamont-Doherty Multi-Channel Seismic system during R/V Marcus G. Langseth expedition MGL1521 conducted in 2015 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Emilie Hooft; Investigators: Dr. Anne Becel). These data files are of SEGD format and include Multi-Channel Seismic Reflection shot data that have not been processed. Data were acquired as part of the projects: Crustal Magma Plumbing of the Santorini Volcanic System and Santorini Seismic Experiment, and funding was provided by NSF grants: OCE16-07104 and OCE14-59794.

Underway Hydrographic, Weather and Ship-state Data (JGOFS) from the Mid-Atlantic Ridge Spreading Center (Southern) acquired during the Nathaniel B. Palmer expedition NBP1508 (2015)

This data set was acquired with a ship-based Fluorometer, Thermosalinograph, Navigation system, Echosounder Sonar, and Meteorological Sensor during Nathaniel B. Palmer expedition NBP1508 conducted in 2015 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Andreas Thurnherr). These data files are of JGOFS (ASCII) format and include Temperature, Fluorescence, Salinity, Conductivity, Bathymetry, Navigation, Meteorological, Infrared Radiation, and Visible Radiation data and were processed after data collection. This data set was created from calibrated data decimated at 1-minute intervals. Several fields are derived measurements from more than a single raw input.

Raw towed Digital Camera Data (JPEG format) from the East Pacific Rise at 9N acquired during the Atlantis expedition AT15-06 (2006)

This data set was acquired with a towed Nikon Coolpix 995 Digital Camera on TowCam during Atlantis expedition AT15-06 conducted in 2006 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Karen Von Damm; Investigator(s): Dr. Daniel Fornari and Dr. S. Adam Soule). These data files are of JPEG Image format and include Photograph data that have not been processed. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): RESET06: Ridge 2000 Atlantis/Alvin Response to 9N ISS Eruption, and funding was provided by NSF grant(s): OCE03-27126. Near-bottom Magnetics Data from the Juan de Fuca Spreading Center acquired with AUV ABE during Atlantis expedition AT11-14 (2004)

This data set was acquired with a Develco Magnetometer on the AUV ABE during Atlantis expedition AT11-14 conducted in 2004 (Chief Scientist: Dr. Russell McDuff). These data files are of Text File (ASCII) format and include Magnetic Field data that have not been processed. Data were acquired as part of the project(s): REVEL Project and Sea Breeze: Fluxes of Heat and Salt from Endeavour Segment Vent Fields, and funding was provided by NSF grant(s): OCE02-42736 and OCE02-43307.
